Obtaining a previous chest x ray for comparison in the patient with a solitary pulmonary nodule can save the patient the expense  discomfort  and possible morbidity of invasive diagnostic procedures if it can be shown that the lesion has been stable for several years 
Patients with stable benign pulmonary lesions can be given a copy of their chest x rays to keep at home 
One of the most frustrating circumstances is to find a lesion on a current chest x ray that was probably present on a previous x ray  but the previous x ray has been misplaced or destroyed  and the stability of the lesion cannot be proved 
